Program: Discovery
Title: AAAS anniversary
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx2n
Last Broadcast Date: 16 February 1998
The 150th anniversary meeting of the American Association for the Advancement of Science. An update on the Aids patient that received a bone marrow transplant from a baboon. The success of the surgery could help patients with other diseases, including many auto immune illnesses.